XML-TreePP-Editor
===============================

This module is used for editing a XML::TreePP parsed XML Document.

EXAMPLE

To use stand-alone:

    use strict;
    use XML::TreePP;
    use XML::TreePP::Editor;
    
    my $tpp = XML::TreePP->new();
    my $tree = $tpp->parse('file.xml');
    my $tppe = new XML::TreePP::Editor();
    $tppe->replace( $tree, '/path[2]/element[2]/edit', { '-myattribute' => "new value" } );
    $tppe->insert( $tree, '.', { <new node> } );


INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install


DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

    XML::TreePP
    XML::TreePP::XMLPath >= 0.60
    Data::Dump


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

    http://www.codepin.org/project/perlmod/XML-TreePP-Editor


